WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.660
I'm one of the many volunteers around the globe that makes this event happen.

00:04.980 --> 00:08.280
I often get asked why I choose to invest my time here.

00:08.280 --> 00:09.640
The answer is simple.

00:10.120 --> 00:13.600
Design competitions are unique and they work.

00:13.960 --> 00:18.180
There is nothing else like them in the education sphere.

00:18.780 --> 00:25.080
We provide high school students the opportunity to learn what it's like to work in the space sector

00:25.080 --> 00:32.740
and give them the chance to practice hands-on STEM well before university, let alone the workplace.

00:33.060 --> 00:37.200
And if you want an example of the success of our events, look no further.

00:38.260 --> 00:38.840
That's right.

00:39.400 --> 00:45.260
Back in 2003, I was one of the team members that was invited to the Kennedy Space Center

00:45.260 --> 00:49.220
as the first ever finalist team from the Southern Hemisphere.

00:49.840 --> 00:52.600
And at the time, I can remember I was at high school.

00:52.600 --> 00:57.100
I wasn't sure if I wanted to study law or engineering when I went to university.

00:57.940 --> 01:03.560
During the ISSDC finals, not only was I mentored by an engineer who had worked on Apollo,

01:04.140 --> 01:09.440
but I spent a whole weekend being around other students just like me.

01:09.920 --> 01:13.320
And from that moment on, law was out, engineering was in,

01:13.740 --> 01:19.680
and I'm now where I am today in no small part due to my experience at the ISSDC finals.

01:19.680 --> 01:22.920
So, why do I volunteer?

01:23.700 --> 01:26.600
Because this event changed my life.

01:27.000 --> 01:31.960
And if I can give back and help just one student change their life, then it's worth it.

